Package: charm
Type: Package
Title: Analysis of DNA methylation data from CHARM microarrays
Version: 0.9.18
Date: 2009-12-21
Author: Martin Aryee, Peter Murakami, Srinivasan Yegnasubramanian, Rafael Irizarry
Maintainer: Martin Aryee <aryee@jhu.edu>
Depends: R(>= 2.10.0), Biobase, oligo, oligoClasses, fields, SQN, snow
Imports: preprocessCore, methods, genefilter, affxparser, stats, Biostrings, IRanges, ACME, ff, bit, spatial, siggenes, gtools
Suggests: pd.feinberg.hg18.me.hx1, BSgenome, BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg18, org.Hs.eg.db,  BSgenome.Mmusculus.UCSC.mm8, org.Mm.eg.db
Description: This package implements analysis tools for DNA methylation microarrays. It identifies significantly methylated regions, finds differentially methylated regions between samples, calculates percentage methylation estimates and includes array quality assessment tools.
License: LGPL (>= 2.0)
LazyLoad: yes
biocViews: Microarray, Bioinformatics
